article.description: Curtis Holland III had a career-high 25 points as High Point rolled past Belmont Abbey 92-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Holland III powers High Point past Belmont Abbey, 92-66
article.linkText: Holland III powers High Point past Belmont Abbey, 92-66
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Curtis Holland III had a career-high 25 points as High Point rolled past Belmont Abbey 92-66 on Saturday. Holland III made 6 of 9 3-pointers. Jamal Wright had 13 points for High Point (3-9). John-Michael Wright added 11 points. Cliff Thomas Jr. had 11 points for the home team. The 92 points were a season best for High Point, which also registered a season-high 26 assists. Sean Halloran had 13 points for the Crusaders. Romeao Ferguson added 11 points. Quest Aldridge had 11 points. High Point plays Campbell on the road next Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
